i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSince the support life of my OnePlus 8T's official ROM is about to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iend, I flashed Nameless OS, a Lineage OS based third party Android		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iROM, onto my phone. But after flashing the ROM, I found that my China		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iTelecom SIM card cannot roam on the 4G network of local mobile service		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iproviders, only 2G or 3G work. Since the local providers are recently		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ishutting down 2G and 3G networks, the roaming cellular signal strength		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iis really bad. I experience a high latency on receiving or sending		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
imessages, nor can I use VoLTE to make calls normally.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iI tested other Lineage OS based third party ROMS, and experienced the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isame problem.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iAfter numerous attempts, I found that the problem **seems to be** with		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe phone's APN settings. I use the term **seems to be** because while		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ichanging APN settings fixed my problem, I have no idea why this works,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
inor am I sure this is the correct way to fix it.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iHere are my steps to resolve the problem:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i1. Enter phone settings - SIMs - China Telecom - Access Point Name		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   settings.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i2. Select "中国电信 NET 设置" (`ctnet`, China Telecom NET Settings) to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   manage detailed options.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i3. Change `APN Type` to: `default,supl,dun,ims`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - The original value is `default,supl,dun`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i4. Click the three-dot menu on top right, and select Save.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i5. Select the radio button on the right of `ctnet`.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i6. Turn off the phone, wait a few minutes, and then turn it on again.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
